{"key":"post-6322688","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6322688</id>\n<content>It usually decreases yield to do that.  Mushroom substrates fruit best when they are steadily losing moisture.  If you install a wick, or lay them directly on moist perlite, they saturate, then fruit poorly, if at all.  Flushing, followed by an overnight soak has shown to provide the best yields indoors.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6322740</next>\n<prev>6322663</prev>\n<first>6322644</first>\n<last>6322898</last>\n<when>1164942794</when>\n<utime>12/01/06 05:13 AM</utime>\n</post>"}